  "id": "api/core/testing/fakeAsync",
  "title": "fakeAsync",
  "contents": "<article>\n  <div class=\"breadcrumb-container\">\n    <div class=\"breadcrumb\">\n      <script type=\"application/ld+json\">\n        {\n          \"@context\": \"http://schema.org\",\n          \"@type\": \"BreadcrumbList\",\n          \"itemListElement\": [\n            { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 1, \"item\": { \"@id\": \"https://angular.io/api\", \"name\": \"API\" } },\n            { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 2, \"item\": { \"@id\": \"https://angular.io/api/core\", \"name\": \"@angular/core\" } },\n            { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 3, \"item\": { \"@id\": \"https://angular.io/api/core/testing\", \"name\": \"@angular/core/testing\" } },\n            { \"@type\": \"ListItem\", \"position\": 4, \"item\": { \"@id\": \"https://angular.io/api/core/testing/fakeAsync\", \"name\": \"fakeAsync\" } }\n          ]\n        }\n      </script>\n        <a href=\"/api\">API</a> > <a href=\"api/core\">@angular/core</a> > <a href=\"api/core/testing\">@angular/core/testing</a>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"github-links\">\n  <a href=\"https://github.com/angular/angular/tree/17.3.12/packages/core/testing/src/fake_async.ts#L33-L62\" aria-label=\"View Source\" title=\"View Source\"><i class=\"material-icons\" aria-hidden=\"true\" role=\"img\">code</i></a>\n</div>\n  </div>\n  <header class=\"api-header\">\n    <h1 id=\"fakeasync\">fakeAsync<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/core/testing/fakeAsync#fakeasync\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h1>\n    <label class=\"api-type-label function\">function</label>\n  </header>\n  <aio-toc class=\"embedded\"></aio-toc>\n\n  <div class=\"api-body\">\n  <section class=\"short-description\">\n    <p>Wraps a function to be executed in the <code><a href=\"api/core/testing/fakeAsync\" class=\"code-anchor\">fakeAsync</a></code> zone:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Microtasks are manually executed by calling <code><a href=\"api/core/testing/flushMicrotasks\" class=\"code-anchor\">flushMicrotasks</a>()</code>.</li>\n<li>Timers are synchronous; <code><a href=\"api/core/testing/tick\" class=\"code-anchor\">tick</a>()</code> simulates the asynchronous passage of time.</li>\n</ul>\n\n    <p><a href=\"api/core/testing/fakeAsync#description\">See more...</a></p>\n  </section>\n\n  <div class=\"overload-info\">\n  <code-example language=\"ts\" hidecopy=\"true\" class=\"no-box api-heading\"> <span class=\"member-name\"><a href=\"api/core/testing/fakeAsync\" class=\"code-anchor\">fakeAsync</a></span>(fn: Function): (...args: any[]) => any</code-example>\n\n  <h6 class=\"no-anchor\" id=\"parameters\">Parameters</h6>\n  <table class=\"is-full-width list-table parameters-table function-overload-parameters\">\n  <tbody>\n    <tr class=\"function-overload-parameter\">\n      <td class=\"param-name\">\n        <a id=\"\"></a>\n        <code>fn</code>\n      </td>\n      <td class=\"param-type\"><code>Function</code></td>\n      <td class=\"param-description\">\n        <p>The function that you want to wrap in the <code><a href=\"api/core/testing/fakeAsync\" class=\"code-anchor\">fakeAsync</a></code> zone.</p>\n\n      </td>\n    </tr>\n  </tbody>\n</table>\n  <h6 class=\"no-anchor\" id=\"returns\">Returns</h6>\n  <p><code>(...args: any[]) => any</code>: The function wrapped to be executed in the <code><a href=\"api/core/testing/fakeAsync\" class=\"code-anchor\">fakeAsync</a></code> zone.\nAny arguments passed when calling this returned function will be passed through to the <code>fn</code>\nfunction in the parameters when it is called.</p>\n\n</div>\n\n\n\n<section class=\"description\">\n  <h2 id=\"description\">Description<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/core/testing/fakeAsync#description\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n  <p>If there are any pending timers at the end of the function, an exception is thrown.</p>\n<p>Can be used to wrap <code>inject()</code> calls.</p>\n  <p>Further information is available in the <a href=\"api/core/testing/fakeAsync#usage-notes\">Usage Notes...</a></p>\n</section>\n\n\n<section class=\"usage-notes\">\n  <h2 id=\"usage-notes\">Usage notes<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/core/testing/fakeAsync#usage-notes\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h2>\n  <h3 id=\"example\">Example<a title=\"Link to this heading\" class=\"header-link\" aria-hidden=\"true\" href=\"api/core/testing/fakeAsync#example\"><i class=\"material-icons\">link</i></a></h3>\n<code-example path=\"core/testing/ts/fake_async.ts\" region=\"basic\">\ndescribe('this test', () => {\n  it(\n    'looks <a href=\"api/platform-browser/animations/async\" class=\"code-anchor\">async</a> but is synchronous',\n    &#x3C;any><a href=\"api/core/testing/fakeAsync\" class=\"code-anchor\">fakeAsync</a>((): void => {\n      let flag = false;\n      setTimeout(() => {\n        flag = true;\n      }, 100);\n      expect(flag).toBe(false);\n      <a href=\"api/core/testing/tick\" class=\"code-anchor\">tick</a>(50);\n      expect(flag).toBe(false);\n      <a href=\"api/core/testing/tick\" class=\"code-anchor\">tick</a>(50);\n      expect(flag).toBe(true);\n    }),\n  );\n});\n\n</code-example>\n\n</section></div>\n</article>\n\n<!-- links to this doc:\n - api/core/testing\n - api/core/testing/flush\n - api/core/testing/tick\n - guide/forms-overview\n - guide/testing-components-scenarios\n - guide/testing-utility-apis\n - guide/upgrade-setup\n-->\n<!-- links from this doc:\n - /api\n - api/core\n - api/core/testing\n - api/core/testing/fakeAsync#description\n - api/core/testing/fakeAsync#example\n - api/core/testing/fakeAsync#fakeasync\n - api/core/testing/fakeAsync#usage-notes\n - api/core/testing/flushMicrotasks\n - api/core/testing/tick\n - api/platform-browser/animations/async\n - https://github.com/angular/angular/tree/17.3.12/packages/core/testing/src/fake_async.ts#L33-L62\n-->"
}